Character.isLetter(char c): Returns true if the specified character is a letter.

Character.isDigit(char c): Returns true if the specified character is a digit.

Character.isLetterOrDigit(char c): Returns true if the specified character is a letter or digit.

Character.isWhitespace(char c): Returns true if the specified character is whitespace.

Character.isUpperCase(char c): Returns true if the specified character is uppercase.

Character.isLowerCase(char c): Returns true if the specified character is lowercase.


Character.toUpperCase(char c): Converts the specified character to uppercase.

Character.toLowerCase(char c): Converts the specified character to lowercase.

Character.toString(char c) or String.valueOf(char c): Returns a String object representing the specified character.


Character.compare(char x, char y): Compares two char values numerically.
